I think this also broke building the protoc artifact on Linux
https://kokoro.corp.google.com/job/grpc/job/ubuntu/job/master/job/grpc_build_artifacts/400/

C++ build was broken because the compiler doesn't support ref-qualifiers even compiled with --std=c++11. I checked the compiler support list:
GCC >= 4.8.1
CLANG >= 2.9
INTEL >= 14.0
MSVC >= Nov 2013 CTP

I think most of them are released in 2013. It's 5 years now, can we update kokoro to a newer compiler?
This should be fixed now. Please help verify with the https://github.com/google/protobuf/releases/tag/v3.4.0rc3
